headline: Prediction: These 2 Stocks Will Be Worth More Than Tesla in the Next 5 Years
summary: Tesla (NASDAQ: TSLA) is currently the eighth-largest company in the world with a market cap of just over $1.05 trillion as of this writing.  The results of the U.S. elections have helped drive Tesla's share price higher, thanks to the belief that CEO Elon Musk's close relationship with President-Elect Donald Trump could benefit the electric vehicle (EV) manufacturer during the new administration.  Tesla stock's underperformance through most of 2024 can be attributed to growing competition that's bringing down its delivery numbers, as well as the company's failure to impress investors with the recent unveiling of the Cybercab.
